{"bill":{"bill_id":1639269,"change_hash":"7b63369c3dc534ccc05b35903c9466d0","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/HB1437\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+HB1437","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-06","progress":[{"date":"2022-12-19","event":1},{"date":"2022-12-19","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-02","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-06","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-08","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-16","event":10}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"HB1437","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":7,"current_body":"S","current_body_id":8,"title":"Installation, etc., of devices in highway right-of-way; law-enforcement purposes, regulation.","description":"Installation, maintenance, and operation of devices in highway right-of-way for law-enforcement purposes; regulation authority; civil penalty. Provides that the authority of the Commonwealth Transportation Board to make regulations for the use of systems of state highways includes the use of devices in the right-of-way of such highways for law-enforcement purposes. The bill authorizes the Department of State Police or chief law-enforcement officer of a locality to install, maintain, and operate devices for law-enforcement purposes on highways maintained by VDOT. The bill requires that all data collected by such devices be purged and not retained later than 30 days after collection unless such data is being used in an active law-enforcement investigation. The bill prohibits the use of such data to enforce speed limits, traffic regulations, tolling requirements, or high-occupancy vehicle requirements. Installation, maintenance, and operation of devices in highway right-of-way for law-enforcement purposes; regulation authority; civil penalty. Provides that the authority of the Commonwealth Transportation Board to make regulations for the use of systems of state highways includes the use of devices in the right-of-way of such highways for law-enforcement purposes. The bill authorizes the Department of State Police or chief law-enforcement officer of a locality to install, maintain, and operate devices for law-enforcement purposes on highways maintained by VDOT. The bill requires that all data collected by such devices be purged and not retained later than 30 days after collection unless such data is being used in an active law-enforcement investigation. The bill prohibits the use of such data to enforce speed limits, traffic regulations, tolling requirements, or high-occupancy vehicle requirements.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2022-12-19","committee_id":159,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Transportation"},{"date":"2023-01-13","committee_id":3886,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Transportation: Subcommittee #2"},{"date":"2023-02-08","committee_id":170,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Transportation"}],"history":[{"date":"2022-12-19","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23102005D","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2022-12-19","action":"Referred to Committee on Transportation","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-13","action":"Assigned Transportation sub: Subcommittee #2 Transportation Infrastructure and Funding","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-31","action":"Subcommittee recommends reporting with substitute (7-Y 0-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-02","action":"Reported from Transportation with substitute (20-Y 2-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-02","action":"Committee substitute printed 23105521D-H1","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-0